Takemichi Hanagaki is a freelancer that's reached the absolute pits of despair in his life. He finds out that the only girlfriend he ever had in his life that he dated in middle school, Hinata Tachibana, had been killed by the ruthless Tokyo Manji Gang.
The day after hearing about her death, he's standing on the station platform and ends up being pushed over onto the tracks by a herd of people. He closes his eyes thinking he's about to die, but when he opens his eyes back up, he somehow had gone back in time 12 years.
Now that he's back living the best days of his life, Takemichi decides to get revenge on his life by saving his girlfriend and changing himself that he'd been running away from.
(Source: Crunchyroll)

Unable to hear, speak, or wield a sword, Prince Bojji doesn’t seem like a typical heir to the throne—and his kingdom agrees. But his fateful encounter with Kage, a shadow on the ground, gives him his first true friend. The two set off on a grand adventure and, together, form a bond that can overcome any obstacle...even being king.
(Source: Funimation)
Mama Tomo to Sodateru Love Come

Komamoto Kyota is a high school boy who dotes on his 3-year-old sister. His parents both work, so he handles all the housework and childcare at home. Akiyama Sumi is a beautiful, smart, but solitary girl whose intimidating presence keeps everyone at arm's length. When Kyota went to his sister's kindergarten entrance ceremony, he found Sumi there with flushed cheeks, snapping pictures like a pro photographer. "Gosh, how adorable...... she is!" They became friends and gradually grew closer as they learned that they are both taking care of younger siblings. They cook together, help each other pick up the kids from kindergarten, and go on holiday outings. Yes, their relationship is truly that of "mommy's friend." A romantic comedy about child-raising!
(Source: Gagaga Bunko, translated)
Tomodachi no Ushiro de Kimi to Kossori Te wo Tsunagu. Dare ni mo Ienai Koi wo Suru.
Comedy, Drama, Romance, Slice of Life
